{"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"A simple reference counted data type representing an immutable sequence of","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"zero or more bytes from an unspecified origin.","type":"text"}],"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Bytes","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The purpose of a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GBytes"},{"type":"text","text":" is to keep the memory region that it holds"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"alive for as long as anyone holds a reference to the bytes.  When","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the last reference count is dropped, the memory is released. Multiple","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"unrelated callers can use byte data in the "},{"code":"GBytes","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" without coordinating"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"their activities, resting assured that the byte data will not change or"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"move while they hold a reference.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A ","type":"text"},{"code":"GBytes","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" can come from many different origins that may have","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"different procedures for freeing the memory region.  Examples are","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"memory from [func"},{"code":"GLib.malloc","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"], from memory slices, from a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[struct"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MappedFile","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"] or memory from other allocators."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GBytes"},{"text":" work well as keys in [struct","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/HashTable"},{"type":"text","text":"]. Use"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"[method","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.Bytes.equal","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"] and [method","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.Bytes.hash","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"] as parameters to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.HashTable.new"},{"type":"text","text":"] or [func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.HashTable.new_full"},{"text":"].","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GBytes"},{"text":" can also be used as keys in a [struct","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Tree","type":"reference"},{"text":"] by passing the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"code":"GLib.Bytes.compare","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] function to [ctor"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.Tree.new"},{"type":"text","text":"]."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The data pointed to by this bytes must not be modified. For a mutable"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"array of bytes see [struct","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ByteArray","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"]. Use"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"code":"GLib.Bytes.unref_to_array","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] to create a mutable array for a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GBytes"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"sequence. To create an immutable ","type":"text"},{"code":"GBytes","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" from a mutable","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[struct"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ByteArray"},{"type":"text","text":"], use the [func"},{"code":"GLib.ByteArray.free_to_bytes","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"]","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"function.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Bytes","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" type acts as a reference-counted owner of an underlying ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GBytes"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It provides the methods that can operate on this data type through ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/BytesProtocol","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" conformance."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Bytes","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" as a strong reference or owner of a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GBytes"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"}]},{"name":"Note","type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/BytesRef","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" (instead of "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Bytes","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":") for a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying "},{"code":"GBytes","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"style":"note"}]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/bytes"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"metadata":{"role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Bytes"}],"roleHeading":"Class","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"externalID":"s:4GLib5BytesC","fragments":[{"kind":"keywo